  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Add the <strong>sausages</strong> to a <strong>tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray </p><p>Put them in the oven for 20-25 min or until they are browned</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/609__step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/609__step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/609__step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/609__step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/609__step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the sausages are in the oven, peel and finely slice the <strong>red onions</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced red onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Cook for 5 min, or until the onion has softened</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/609-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/609-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/609-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/609-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/609-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut the <strong>waxy potatoes</strong> into quarters</p><p>Add them to a pot, cover with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Bring to a boil over a high heat and cook for 20 min or until fork-tender</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/609-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/609-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/609-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/609-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/609-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the red onion has softened, add 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong>, the <strong>onion marmalade</strong>, <strong>red wine vinegar</strong>, <strong>Henderson's Relish</strong> and 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>water </strong>to the pan</p><p>Reduce the heat to its lowest setting and cook the onions for a further 20 min, or until they're sticky and sweet – these are your <strong>caramelised onions</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/609-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/609-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/609-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/609-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/609-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the onions are caramelising, combine the <strong>mayo</strong>, <strong>wholegrain mustard</strong> and <strong>white wine vinegar</strong> with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>pepper</strong> in a small bowl – this is your <strong>dressing</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
